 Cambridge graduate Svetlana Lokhova was a ` resilient person ' driven to a mental breakdown by work colleagues at the bank .
A employment tribunal found .
Workmates falsely accused her of being a cocaine user , dubbed her ` Miss Bonkers ' and said she was hired by bank only because of her looks .
She was awarded £ 3.14 million for lost earnings , £ 44,000 for hurt feelings .